3. CSS styling (style.css)
This styles the HTML to create a visually appealing website. 
css
/*  General styles  */
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
}

.container {
    width: 80%;
    margin: auto;
    overflow: hidden;
}

/*  Header and Navigation  */
header {
    background: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1rem 0;
}

header h1 {
    float: left;
    margin: 0;
}

header ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    float: right;
}

header li {
    display: inline;
    padding: 0 20px;
}

header a {
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
}

/*  Hero section  */
.hero {
    min-height: 400px;
    background: #f4f4f4;
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 100px;
}

/*  Sections  */
.menu-section, .about-section, .reservation-section, .contact-section {
    padding: 20px 0;
}

/*  Footer  */
footer {
    background: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem 0;
}

/*  Responsive Design (adjust as needed)  */
@media(max-width: 768px) {
    header h1, header ul {
        float: none;
        text-align: center;
    }

    header li {
        padding: 10px;
        display: block;
    }
}
Use code with caution.

4. JavaScript functionality (script.js)
This adds basic interactivity, like smooth scrolling. 
js
// Smooth scrolling for navigation links
$(document).ready(function () { 
    $("a").on("click", function (event) {
        if (this.hash !== "") {
            event.preventDefault();

            var hash = this.hash;

            $("html, body").animate({
                scrollTop: $(hash).offset().top,
            }, 800, function () {
                window.location.hash = hash;
            });
        }
    });
});
